# Changelog

All notable changes to DINOForge will be documented in this file.

The format is based on [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/),
and this project adheres to [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html).

## [Unreleased]

### Fixed ŌĆö Asset Swap: cims / buildings / aircraft now reskin (#986)
- **Wrong swap archetypes for cims, buildings, and aircraft (live `0 succeeded` ŌåÆ `39 succeeded`)** ŌĆö The #975 archetype guesses returned 0 RenderMesh-bearing entities, so the `RenderMesh AND <archetype>` swap query matched nothing and these categories logged `batch complete ŌĆö 0 succeeded, 30 failed` while ground units swapped fine. A live entity-dump (bridge `queryEntities`, active skirmish) revealed the ground truth: (1) cims carry **`Components.Citizen`** (live count 58) with RenderMesh on the same entity ŌĆö the previous guess `Components.Worker` matched only 2 singletons; (2) DINO **buildings** carry `Components.BuildingBase` (575) but **no RenderMesh on the parent** ŌĆö the mesh lives on a CHILD entity referenced via `Unity.Entities.LinkedEntityGroup`; (3) `aerial_fighter` resolved to `DINOForge.Runtime.Aviation.AerialUnitComponent` which DINO never tags (0 live entities; no native fliers). Fixes: cims/worker/citizen ŌåÆ `Components.Citizen` (`PackStatMappings`); `aerial_fighter` swap archetype ŌåÆ `Components.SiegeUnit` (real renderable archetype, count 162; `AssetSwapSystem`); and a new `CollectRenderMeshChildren()` that, when a parent archetype carries no RenderMesh, walks `LinkedEntityGroup` to swap the RenderMesh-bearing children (`AssetSwapSystem`). Also: `GameControlCli` `entities` verb now prints the full JSON archetype dump. Live-verified after deploy: warfare-starwars pass `batch complete ŌĆö 39 succeeded, 13 failed` (was 0 succeeded); `sw-cis-droid-pilot` cim `swapped 51/51 result=True`; `sw-cis-command-center` / `sw-cis-droid-factory` / `sw-clone-barracks` / `sw-rep-vehicle-bay` buildings each `swapped 100/100` via the child-walk. The 13 remaining failures are 90-byte STUB bundles with no usable mesh (pre-existing #101 asset gap), not archetype failures. Survey: `docs/sessions/entity-archetype-survey-20260531.md`. Files: `src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`, `src/Runtime/Bridge/PackStatMappings.cs`, `src/Tools/GameControlCli/Program.cs`.

### Fixed ŌĆö Game-Breaking Regression
- **`startGame` RPC corrupting native `GameWorldLoaderSystem` (NRE flood)** ŌĆö The `startGame` RPC in `GameBridgeServer.HandleStartGame` (introduced by nav-scripter commit 65cddb03) created a bare `Components.SingletonComponents.BeginGameWorldLoadingSingleton` ECS entity with empty/unpopulated fields to programmatically trigger world-load. DINO's native `Systems.GameWorldLoaderSystem.OnUpdate` then called `GetSingleton<>()` expecting the managed component (save path / map id / load params) populated, got null/empty, and threw a `NullReferenceException` **every frame** in `InitializationSystemGroup` ŌĆö flooding the log and breaking world-load. Fix (safe revert / Option A): the RPC is now a **no-op** that returns `{success:false, disabled:true}` and never creates the bare entity; normal menu-driven world-load is unaffected. To re-enable programmatic world-load, all required singleton fields must be populated with valid values before entity creation. Live-verified: GameWorldLoaderSystem NRE count went from flooding to **0**, game loads a world normally (49014 entities, advancing frames). File: `src/Runtime/Bridge/GameBridgeServer.cs` (~L1841).

### Added ŌĆö Autonomous Navigation
- **NavigationScripter + `navigateToGameplay` RPC / `game_navigate_to_gameplay` MCP tool** ŌĆö Scripts the full main-menu ŌåÆ skirmish UI sequence (PLAY/SANDBOX/SKIRMISH ŌåÆ optional map/scenario select ŌåÆ START) in-process, composing the EventSystem pointer driver (#972) and reliable FrameCapture (#980). Each step resolves an ordered candidate-selector list (tolerant of DINO label variance), fires a real EventSystem pointer click, waits for a next-screen / world-ready condition (no fixed sleeps), and captures a verification PNG; a final gameplay-camera frame is captured on success. Exposes a Bridge RPC, `GameClient.NavigateToGameplayAsync`, the `navigate-to-gameplay` GameControlCli verb, and the `game_navigate_to_gameplay` MCP tool ŌĆö closing the gap that let RPCs load a world but never fire the menuŌåÆlevel transition, so verify-agents can now autonomously reach + capture in-game states. Flow map: `docs/sessions/nav-scripter-flow-map-20260530.md`.

