### Fixed
- **AssetSwap THE "units look native" fix: mesh-substring filter was rejecting 100% of entities (#101).** Even after the reflection fix, every unit stayed native ŌĆö live logs showed `swapped 0/100 entities (skipped 100 non-matching meshes)` for every mapping. Root cause: with an authoritative archetype filter already applied, the SECONDARY mesh-name substring filter (`VanillaMappingToMeshSubstrings`, e.g. `Swordsman`/`Militia`/`Knight`) was used as a hard *reject*, but those hand-guessed substrings do not match DINO's real mesh vocabulary (`swordsmen`, `royal_sword_2`, `bomj_*`, `harpy_*`, `undead_*`, `natives_*`), so 0 entities passed and no mesh was ever written. Fix: when an archetype filter is present it is authoritative ŌĆö swap every entity the narrowed `EntityQuery` returns and ignore the substrings (which now serve only as a fallback targeting signal when there is no archetype filter). Live-verified: `swapped 100/100 ŌĆ” skipped 0` across MeleeUnit/RangeUnit/SiegeUnit/Aerial (66 positive swaps, 0 zero-swaps) ŌĆö units now render their Star Wars meshes. (`src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`)
  - **Merge-gap re-verification (2026-05-31, branch `reconcile3/converge-20260531`):** reconcile-3 had cherry-picked an *earlier* #981 commit instead of the real fix, so the deployed build (`900797F0`) still logged `swapped 0/100 ŌĆ” skipped 100 non-matching meshes`. Re-cherry-picked `f1f5f1e5`+`dd52c960`+`8a690a1e` and redeployed (DLL `1BDC999C`). Live log on the redeploy: **132 `result=True` ground-unit swaps, 132 positive `swapped N/M` events (90├Ś100/100, plus 76/76, 64/64, 35/35, 31/31, 18/18, 15/15), ZERO `swapped 0/` and ZERO `skipped 100 non-matching` lines.** Distinct units swapped: sw-clone-trooper-republic, sw-jedi-knight, sw-general-grievous, sw-cis-droideka, sw-b1-battle-droid, sw-at-te-walker, etc. Buildings + aerial still log `result=False` at main menu (no building/aircraft entities spawned there) ŌĆö separate known gap.
- **AssetSwap ground-unit swap: ComponentTypeŌåÆInt32 reflection error (#101, "units look native" BUG A).** `AssetSwapSystem.TrySwapRenderMeshFromBundle`'s archetype-narrowed path threw at runtime ŌĆö `Object of type 'Unity.Entities.ComponentType' cannot be converted to type 'System.Int32'` ŌåÆ `result=False` ("swapped 0/100" for ground units e.g. `sw-cis-magna-guard`). DINO's Unity 2021.3 `EntityManager` exposes the non-generic `GetSharedComponentData` in TWO overloads ŌĆö `(Entity, ComponentType)` AND `(Entity, int typeIndex)` ŌĆö and the `FirstOrDefault` lookup (which accepts either) could bind the Int32 overload, then invoking it with a boxed `ComponentType` threw. Fix: detect the bound overload's second-parameter type and pass `ComponentType.TypeIndex` (int) when it wants `System.Int32`, else the `ComponentType`. (`src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`)
- **AssetSwap aerial units: `aerial_fighter` no longer stuck in DIAGNOSTIC MODE (#101, BUG B).** `vanilla_mapping='aerial_fighter'` produced no archetype filter (PackStatMappings intentionally maps it to null for stat injection ŌĆö `AerialSpawnSystem` owns aerial behaviour) AND no mesh-name substrings ŌåÆ `sw-tri-fighter`/`sw-nantex-fighter` skipped the swap. Fix: new `AssetSwapSystem.TryResolveSwapArchetype()` resolves `aerial_fighter` to `DINOForge.Runtime.Aviation.AerialUnitComponent` for the visual swap (PackStatMappings stays null so stat injection still defers to `AerialSpawnSystem`); added aerial mesh-name substrings (`Aerial/Air/Flying/Fighter/...`) as a fallback targeting signal so the swap proceeds even before `AerialSpawnSystem` tags the entity. (`src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`, `src/Runtime/Bridge/PackStatMappings.cs`)
- **Projectile recolour: same ComponentTypeŌåÆInt32 reflection bug in BlasterBolt (#101).** `ProjectileMeshSwapSystem.RecolourProjectile` ([BlasterBolt]) had the identical `GetSharedComponentData` overload bug, throwing ~22k `Recolour failed on projectile ŌĆ” cannot be converted to Int32` log lines per run and leaving blaster bolts native-coloured. Same fix: pass `ComponentType.TypeIndex` (int) when the bound overload is `(Entity, int)`. (`src/Runtime/Bridge/ProjectileMeshSwapSystem.cs`)
- **AssetSwap buildings: structures no longer stuck in DIAGNOSTIC MODE (#101, building fix).** Pack buildings (e.g. `sw-cis-command-center`, `sw-rep-vehicle-bay`, `sw-cis-droid-factory`) registered their swap with **no** `vanilla_mapping` ŌĆö `BuildingDefinition` had no such field and `ContentLoader` passed null ŌĆö so every SW structure fell into DIAGNOSTIC MODE and kept rendering as the native royal/undead building. Fix: added `BuildingDefinition.VanillaMapping` (YAML `vanilla_mapping`); `ContentLoader` now passes it, defaulting to the generic `building` mapping when omitted; `AssetSwapSystem.TryResolveSwapArchetype()` maps `building` ŌåÆ `Components.BuildingBase` (the universal vanilla building archetype) and a `building` mesh-substring set was added as a refinement. Building stat injection is unaffected (resolution lives in the swap path, not `PackStatMappings`). (`src/SDK/Models/BuildingDefinition.cs`, `src/SDK/ContentLoader.cs`, `src/Runtime/Bridge/AssetSwapSystem.cs`)
- **Star Wars main-menu wallpaper: removed baked-in loading bar (BUG A, #978).** `packs/warfare-starwars/assets/ui/menu_bg.png` was rasterized from a *loading-screen* SVG (`ui/loading-republic.svg`), so a static "LOADING MODULE" caption bar + frozen ~68% progress bar were baked into the bottom of the settled main-menu background ŌĆö a fake progress bar with no load in progress. Added a dedicated clean source `assets/svg/menu-bg.svg` (boot-splash composition minus the lower-third caption/progress layer), re-rendered `menu_bg.png` from it, and repointed `scripts/art/rasterize-menu-takeover.ps1` so the menu wallpaper can never again be generated from a loading SVG.
- **Star Wars loading sequence: live progress layer instead of fake static skeleton (BUG B, #978).** The loading screen previously showed a static image whose progress bar was baked into the background while `LoadingScreenController` pinned the branded overlay on-screen for a fixed `MinVisibleSeconds = 12s` ŌĆö together producing a ~20s frozen "skeleton". Fixes: clean themed loading background (`assets/svg/ui/loading-bg-clean.svg`, baked bar removed); live indeterminate progress ramp + travelling shimmer in `src/Runtime/UI/LoadingScreenController.cs` (real `SetPackProgress` overrides; snaps to 100% only when done); `MinVisibleSeconds` 12sŌåÆ1.5s with readiness-driven `BeginFadeOut`; overlay self-destroys once MainMenu is ready.
- **Star Wars live mesh-swap exits DIAGNOSTIC MODE (#964).** `AssetSwapSystem.TrySwapRenderMeshFromBundle` previously referenced a non-existent `BundleToVanillaMeshMap` and tried to match optional mesh-name substrings by *bundle filename*, so every Star Wars bundle fell into DIAGNOSTIC MODE and no entity swap ran. The optional mesh-name refinement now keys off the request's `vanilla_mapping` value via `VanillaMappingToMeshSubstrings` (aligned 1:1 with `PackStatMappings.VanillaMappingToComponentType`). DIAGNOSTIC MODE is now entered only when there is **no** targeting signal at all ŌĆö neither a resolved archetype filter nor mesh-name substrings ŌĆö so a populated `vanilla_mapping` (already present on all 30 SW units; aerial intentionally skipped) lets the archetype-narrowed swap proceed. The mesh-name filter loop is guarded so archetype-only mode swaps every entity the narrowed query returns. Mesh/material lookup remains robust via `ResolveReplacementAssets` (exact-name ŌåÆ prefab renderer ŌåÆ `LoadAllAssets<Mesh>/<Material>` fallback ŌĆö never the bundle key). Key audit: all 30 SW unit `visual_asset` keys resolve in `addressables.yaml`; 14 reference real (>40KB) bundles. Runtime builds netstandard2.0 exit 0; all 31 AssetSwap tests pass.
- **Full-world Star Wars conversion Phase 1 ŌĆö world-entity swap layer for cims, castle, and all buildings (#975).** Extends the #964 archetype-narrowed mesh swap (which only covered combat units) to the rest of the world, since everything in DINO renders via `Unity.Rendering.RenderMesh`.
  - **Gap A ŌĆö building swaps now register WITH a `vanilla_mapping`.** `ContentLoader.RegisterAssetSwaps` previously registered every building swap with a null `vanilla_mapping`, so the runtime `AssetSwapSystem` saw "no targeting signal" and skipped them in DIAGNOSTIC MODE. It now resolves a mapping per building in priority order ŌĆö explicit `building.vanilla_mapping` ŌåÆ `building_type` (command/barracks/resource/defense/tower/wall/research) ŌåÆ generic `"building"` ŌĆö and threads it into `AssetSwapRequest.VanillaMapping`. New `BuildingDefinition.VanillaMapping` (`vanilla_mapping:` YAML field) makes the targeting declarative.
  - **Gap B ŌĆö cims (citizens/workers, `bomj_*` meshes) now have a registration path.** Cims are modelled as units carrying `vanilla_mapping: cims`, so the existing unit registration path wires their swap with no new registry or schema. New `packs/warfare-starwars/units/cims.yaml` reskins them to SW worker units (`rep_clone_worker` ŌåÆ Clone Engineer, `cis_worker_droid` ŌåÆ Pilot Droid) using real (non-stub) bundles.
  - **CASTLE / command center** ŌĆö `rep_command_center` and `cis_tactical_center` now carry explicit `vanilla_mapping: command` (ŌåÆ `sw-rep-command-center` / `sw-cis-command-center`).
  - `PackStatMappings.VanillaMappingToComponentType` gained entries for `cims`/`worker`/`citizen` (ŌåÆ `Components.Worker`, candidate archetype ŌĆö verify via entity dump) and `building`/`command`/`barracks`/`resource`/`economy`/`defense`/`tower`/`wall`/`research` (ŌåÆ `Components.BuildingBase`). `AssetSwapSystem.VanillaMappingToMeshSubstrings` gained matching `bomj`/worker and building (castle/barrack/farm/tower/wall/ŌĆ”) mesh-name substrings so swaps still exit DIAGNOSTIC MODE via the secondary mesh-name filter when the archetype type does not resolve. Maps/skybox are Phase 2 (out of scope). Runtime builds netstandard2.0 exit 0; new registration + mapping tests added (`FullWorldConversionSwapTests`, `PackStatInjectorTests`).
- **Reliable in-process frame capture in all game states (menu + in-game + loading) ŌĆö #972.** The screenshot RPC previously called `UnityEngine.ScreenCapture.CaptureScreenshot(path)`, which is **asynchronous**: it only queues a deferred end-of-frame capture and Unity writes the PNG on a later frame. The bridge handler returned `Success=true` the moment the request was queued, without ever confirming a file landed on disk, and DINO's custom PlayerLoop never reliably flushed that deferred capture during active gameplay ŌĆö so the handler reported "saved" while no PNG existed (it happened to work at the main menu where the stock present path still ran). New `src/Runtime/Bridge/FrameCapture.cs` replaces it with a synchronous, blocking capture: a coroutine on a DontDestroyOnLoad host yields `WaitForEndOfFrame`, calls `ScreenCapture.CaptureScreenshotIntoRenderTexture` (which composites **all cameras + Screen-Space-Overlay UI** into a RenderTexture ŌĆö exactly what is on screen), `ReadPixels` it back, vertically flips, `EncodeToPNG`, and `File.WriteAllBytes`. A `ManualResetEventSlim` blocks the calling bridge thread until the file is fully written, so `ScreenshotResult.Success`/`Path` now reflect a real on-disk PNG. Wired into `GameBridgeServer.HandleScreenshot` and the `NativeMenuInjector` file-trigger + auto-checkpoint paths; MCP `game_screenshot` Tier 2 (GameControlCli ŌåÆ named pipe) inherits the fix automatically. Added `MainThreadDispatcher.IsMainThread` so callers already on the main thread skip re-marshalling. Verified live against a loaded world (49,152 entities): non-black 2560├Ś1440 PNGs captured (`docs/screenshots/capture-fix-menu-20260530.png`, `docs/screenshots/capture-fix-ingame-20260530.png`). Unblocks the session recorder (#979) and all autonomous vision-verify.
- **MODS button now a real native-equivalent widget with working hover/press/normal feedback.** The injected MODS button previously "acted like the cursor was never over it" ŌĆö no hover/press/BG visual. Root cause: the clone carried over a transition mode of `None` (DINO defers menu-button visuals to its custom `MainMenuButton : Selectable` script, which was being stripped) and/or had no `targetGraphic`, so Unity's `Selectable` transition had nothing to paint.
  - `NativeUiHelper.CloneButton` now preserves Selectable-derived highlight drivers (`StripNonUiBehaviours(preserveSelectables: true)` + `NeutralizePreservedSelectables`) instead of destroying DINO's `MainMenuButton`, and only severs their click/submit callbacks + navigation so the surviving `Button` owns interaction while native hover visuals can still render.
  - New `NativeUiHelper.EnsureVisibleTransition` forces a `ColorTint` transition (warm-gold SW-palette highlight/pressed tints) whenever the donor's transition was `None`, guaranteeing visible hover/press feedback even when no custom highlight driver survives. Wired into both the Unity-Button path (`NativeMenuInjector.SyncButtonVisualStyle`, after the transition copy) and the Selectable-donor path.
  - `NativeUiHelper.CopySelectableVisualState` (the active DINO `MainMenuButton`-donor path) now also resolves and copies the donor's `targetGraphic` (matched by relative transform path) plus the background `Image` sprite/material/color, so the injected button has a graphic to tint and matching normal-state chrome. The stale dual-`Selectable` (custom + new `Button`) is now removed after the visual-state transfer to stop the two from fighting over pointer events.
  - Live-verified via runtime log: injected button reports `Visual transition after sync: ColorTint (targetGraphic=DINOForge_ModsButton)` (was effectively `None` before).
- **100% page skinning for non-main-menu pages.** `MainMenuThemer` previously skinned only the `MainMenu` canvas, leaving the Options/Settings page, its subpages (GAME/VIDEO/SOUND/CONTROLS/TWITCH), and the game create/select screens rendering as unskinned native. New `MainMenuThemer.ApplyToAuxiliaryMenus` re-skins every active auxiliary menu canvas (color layer: `RestyleSelectables` + label/text recolor + background tint + themed font) the first time each becomes active, tracked by instance id. Driven each pump frame from `Plugin.cs` once a conversion theme is resolved. Live-verified: `AUX-SKIN` applied to `Options` (btn=6 text=171), `SpecialMissions`, `ProfilesList`, `SandBox`, `EndlessMissions`, `CustomMaps`, `Saves`, `Map`, and more.

### Added
- **Real meshes + AssetBundles for 19 previously-stub Star Wars units (#964 / #946 fallback).** Replaced 896/1092-byte stub `model.glb` (and absent meshes) with Blender-generated clean-room parametric silhouettes (walkers, fighters, hovertanks, spider/tripod droids, troopers, gunship), converted to FBX and built into Unity 2021.3.45f1 AssetBundles (filename = `visual_asset` = Addressable key). Covers marquee gaps: `sw-general-grievous`, `sw-rep-at-te-walker`, `sw-tri-fighter`, `sw-aat-walker`/`sw-cis-aat`, `sw-v19-torrent`, `sw-jedi-knight`, `sw-cis-spider-droid`, `sw-rep-laat-gunship`, `sw-droideka`, plus arc/commando/sniper/magna-guard/medical/b1-squad/wall-guard/stap/barc. Bundles are 82ŌĆō153 KB real geometry (not 90-byte stubs); render-proofs in `docs/screenshots/model-previews/sw-procedural/`. Acquisition strategy (Sketchfab token path, BF2/Frostbite extraction steps, OSS/CC0 sources, legal posture) documented in `docs/sessions/sw-asset-acquisition-20260530.md`. New tooling: `unity-assetbundle-builder/generate_sw_procedural.py`, `render_proof.py`, `Assets/Editor/BuildSwMissingBundles.cs`. Placeholder-grade ŌĆö meant to be upgraded by higher-fidelity Sketchfab/BF2 sources when the user supplies a token or runs the extractor.
- **Pack buildings injected into DINO's live build menu (vanilla-slot aliasing).** Defining a building in pack YAML was not enough to make it appear/buildable ŌĆö DINO's build menu is data-driven by compiled config structs (`ScriptableObjectDefinitions.BuildingsCategory` ŌåÆ `BuildingTypeContainer`) keyed by the **closed compiled** `Utility.EnumsStorage.BuildingType` enum, so a brand-new building type cannot be added at runtime. New runtime injection makes pack buildings (warfare-aerial airfields, warfare-starwars `rep_gunship_bay`/`cis_droid_hangar`, warfare-naval) appear + buildable by **aliasing** each onto an existing vanilla buildable slot, then reskinning (mesh-swap, #964) and re-targeting production:
  - `BuildingDefinition.BuildAlias` (`build_alias:` YAML) ŌĆö optional explicit vanilla `BuildingType` to alias onto.
  - `src/Runtime/Bridge/BuildAliasMapper.cs` ŌĆö pure, unit-tested alias resolution (explicit `build_alias`, else auto-map by category/id: ProductionŌåÆ`Stables`, Defense/AntiAirŌåÆ`Tower`, navalŌåÆ`Port`).
  - `src/Runtime/Bridge/BuildMenuInjector.cs` ŌĆö world-ready reflection injector: discovers the live config object holding `List<BuildingsCategory>` (field-shape scan, host-type-agnostic), validates aliases against the live enum, confirms the slot is present in a menu category, and records aliasŌåÆpack-building registrations for the reskin/production layers.
  - `src/Runtime/Bridge/BuildMenuInjectionSystem.cs` ŌĆö one-shot `SystemBase` (SimulationSystemGroup, main-thread, ~30s delay; no MonoBehaviour.Update) that runs the injection in-game.
  - `EntityQueries.ResolveType(string)` helper for resolving game enums / ScriptableObject / UnityEngine types (non-ECS-component CLR types).
  - Wired in `ModPlatform.OnWorldReady` (`GetOrCreateSystem<BuildMenuInjectionSystem>` + `BuildMenuInjector.Initialize`).
  - **Discovery doc**: `docs/sessions/dino-build-catalog-20260530.md` (how DINO's build menu + building catalog work, obtained via live bridge reflection + `DNO.Main.dll` metadata).
  - Tests: `src/Tests/BuildAliasMapperTests.cs` (18 cases).
- **In-process EventSystem input driver (`EventSystemDriver`) ŌĆö programmatically drives DINO's Unity uGUI EventSystem hover/press/click.** Synthetic OS input (SetCursorPos/SendInput/MCP `game_input`) is NOT delivered to DINO's EventSystem (confirmed: even the native Options button shows no hover under synthetic input), which blocked pixel-verification of all interactive UI. Because DINOForge runs inside the game via BepInEx, the new driver bypasses the OS entirely.
  - **`src/Runtime/UI/EventSystemDriver.cs`** ŌĆö resolves a target by selector (reusing `UiSelectorEngine` grammar) or by screen coordinates (via the active `GraphicRaycaster`s), then fires the full pointer lifecycle through `ExecuteEvents` (enter ŌåÆ exit / down ŌåÆ up ŌåÆ click) plus drives `Selectable` state (`OnPointerEnter/Exit/Down/Up` + `SetSelectedGameObject`) so DINO's MainMenuButton highlight driver paints hover/press. Runs on the Unity main thread via `MainThreadDispatcher` (EventSystem is main-thread-only); guards `EventSystem.current != null` (Pattern #235). Button.onClick / Toggle fallbacks included.
  - **Bridge RPC `uiPointer`** (`GameBridgeServer`) ŌĆö `{ target?: selector, x?, y?: screen coords, event: enter|exit|down|up|click|hover|press }`. Client method `GameClient.UiPointerAsync`, CLI `ui-pointer <event> <selector|x=..\ y=..>`, and MCP tool `game_ui_pointer`. This is the in-process path that actually paints hover/press and unblocks vision-verify for interactive UI (#970/#971/#966).
- **In-process Session Recorder (#971) ŌĆö record a real user playthrough for replay + vision-verify.** New `src/Runtime/Capture/SessionRecorder.cs`: pressing **F11** in-game starts/stops recording of a REAL user session. It captures timestamped pointer (move/down/up) and key events, the widget DINO's `EventSystem` actually resolved (top `RaycastAll` hit path + `currentSelectedGameObject`), and periodic/per-event screen frames, writing a replayable **journey record** (`timeline.json` + `manifest.json` + `frames/*.png`) to `BepInEx/dinoforge_recordings/<session-id>/`.
  - **Why:** synthetic OS input (SendInput / `SetCursorPos` / MCP `game_input`) is not delivered to DINO's Unity `EventSystem`, but real user input is ŌĆö so we record once and replay in-process (#972) to unblock autonomous vision-verify for all UI/world tasks.
  - **DINO-ECS-safe:** the per-frame sampler runs on the Unity main thread via PlayerLoop injection (no `Update()`); all `EventSystem.current` reads are null-guarded (Pattern #235); the F11 toggle is detected on a Win32 `GetAsyncKeyState` background thread that only flips a flag; frames reuse the proven `ScreenCapture.CaptureScreenshot` path. `netstandard2.0`; compiled only when the game is installed.
  - **Config** (`[SessionRecorder]` BepInEx section): `Enabled` (default true), `FrameIntervalMs` (500), `CaptureFramePerEvent` (true).
  - **Format + replay/embed mapping:** `docs/capture/session-record-format.md`; JSON Schema `schemas/session-record.schema.json`. Maps cleanly to the in-process replay driver (#972) and to `JourneyViewer.vue` journey embeds (#966).
- **Full-page theme skin via `CanvasReskinner`** (`src/Runtime/UI/CanvasReskinner.cs`) ŌĆö `MainMenuThemer` only themes the MainMenu canvas; the new reskinner walks every OTHER active canvas (Settings + GAME/VIDEO/SOUND/CONTROLS/TWITCH sub-tabs, game create/select) and applies the active total_conversion `ui_theme` colors to each `Selectable` (highlight/press/selected) and `Text`/`TMP_Text` label. Idempotent (per-object marker), re-run on the runtime pump every ~15 frames so lazily-created sub-panels get skinned, and re-armed on scene change via `RunMainMenuInit`. Excludes MainMenu (owned by `MainMenuThemer`) and DINOForge-owned UI.
- **Injected MODS button state-copy now carries the full native frame (#970b)** ŌĆö the donor `MainMenuButton:Selectable` background `Image` (sprite/material/type/color/PPU/preserveAspect) and `targetGraphic` are now copied onto the clone in `NativeUiHelper.CopySelectableVisualState`, and the Image-copy helper in `NativeMenuInjector` now forwards `material`/`pixelsPerUnitMultiplier`/`preserveAspect`. Previously a custom-shader native frame lost its material on the clone, so the MODS button read as flat/non-reactive on hover/press; it now renders normal/hover/press identically to native menu items.
- **Realistic-GFX mode Phase 2 ŌĆö PBR material upgrade for the `High` graphics tier (Manor-Lords-like lift).** Builds on the Phase-1 URP post-process PoC (#976). When `[Graphics] Tier = High`, DINOForge now upgrades swapped unit/building materials to the URP/Lit physically-based shader and bumps quality settings; `Tier = Vanilla` remains a strict passthrough. CODE-READY (visible result needs real PBR textures from #973-BF2 + a deploy).
  - **`GraphicsMaterialUpgrader` (`src/Runtime/Graphics/GraphicsMaterialUpgrader.cs`)** ŌĆö `Upgrade(Material, assetKey)` produces a new `Universal Render Pipeline/Lit` material that carries over the base albedo map + tint and layers in declared PBR maps (albedo `_BaseMap`, metallic+gloss `_MetallicGlossMap`, normal `_BumpMap`, AO `_OcclusionMap`, emission `_EmissionMap`) with the matching shader keywords (`_METALLICSPECGLOSSMAP` / `_NORMALMAP` / `_OCCLUSIONMAP` / `_EMISSION`). Sets a sensible metallic/smoothness baseline even when no maps exist, so surfaces gain proper specular response under High. Graceful fallback to the original material when tier is Vanilla, when URP/Lit is unavailable, or on any error (never throws, never breaks a swap).
  - **`PbrMaterialRegistry` + `PbrTextureSet`** ŌĆö thread-safe registry mapping a pack `visual_asset` key (or material/mesh name) to its declared PBR texture set. The data contract pack loaders / the asset pipeline populate once BF2/#973 PBR textures arrive; until then the registry is empty and the upgrade degrades to a shader-only lift.
  - **AssetSwap hook (#964 path)** ŌĆö `AssetSwapSystem.TrySwapRenderMeshFromBundle` now runs the resolved replacement material through `GraphicsMaterialUpgrader.Upgrade(..., assetName)` before applying it to live RenderMesh entities, so SW-swapped units pick up the PBR upgrade automatically when High is active.
  - **Quality-settings bumps (`GraphicsMode`)** ŌĆö High tier raises shadow resolution (VeryHigh), shadow distance (Ōēź150), cascades (4), and MSAA (4x), captured-and-restored against a vanilla snapshot so toggling back to Vanilla fully reverts. The upgrader's `ActiveTier` is driven from `GraphicsMode` in lock-step with the Phase-1 post-process toggle (reversible).

- **Functional aerial content ŌĆö airports + airplanes (declarative, pack-based).** Added the core aerial gameplay feature on top of the existing Aviation ECS systems (`AerialMovementSystem` / `AerialTargetingSystem` / `AerialSpawnSystem`, driven by `AerialUnitComponent`).
  - **Generic airports (`packs/warfare-aerial/buildings/airfield_buildings.yaml`)** ŌĆö new `airport` (produces Fighter + Interceptor planes), `hangar` (produces Bomber planes, repair bay), and `landing_pad` (produces Interceptors + integrated `AntiAir` defense). Each declares a `production:` block linking it to its airplane units.
  - **Generic airplanes (`packs/warfare-aerial/units/aerial_units.yaml`)** ŌĆö new fixed-wing `aerial_fighter_plane`, `aerial_bomber_plane`, and `aerial_interceptor_plane`, each carrying the `Aerial` behavior_tag (so `AerialUnitMapper` attaches `AerialUnitComponent` on spawn) plus an `aerial:` block (cruise_altitude / ascend / descend); fighter + interceptor are `anti_air: true` interceptors.
  - **Star Wars aerial content (real meshes).** Republic `rep_gunship_bay` (Gunship Landing Platform ŌåÆ produces `rep_laat_gunship` + `rep_v19_torrent`, mesh `sw-rep-gunship-bay`) and CIS `cis_droid_hangar` (Droid Starfighter Hangar ŌåÆ produces `cis_tri_fighter` + `cis_nantex_fighter`, mesh `sw-cis-hangar-bay`); wired existing `cis_vulture_nest` to produce `cis_tri_fighter`. New aerial units `rep_laat_gunship` (mesh `sw-rep-laat-gunship`) and `cis_nantex_fighter` (mesh `sw-nantex-fighter`), both referencing real proven-render bundles.
  - **Tests** ŌĆö extended `AviationStarWarsTests` with airport-produces-aerial-unit and generic-airplane coverage (Groups 7 & 8); updated `Phase3BDroidLODTests` CIS unit count 14ŌåÆ15. All 88 aviation/Phase3B tests pass; PackCompiler `validate` passes for both packs.
- **`warfare-naval` extension pack** ŌĆö New seafaring companion to `warfare-aerial`. An additive engine-extension pack (`type: content`, `classification: engine_extension`, `tags: [extension, naval, warfare]`, `framework_version: ">=0.1.0 <1.0.0"`) that adds naval vessels (Scout Skiff, War Galley) to vanilla DINO factions without replacing them. Together `warfare-aerial` + `warfare-naval` provide the base aerial/naval mechanics that themed total conversions (e.g. `warfare-starwars`) may optionally `depends_on`. Includes `units/naval_units.yaml` and a README with the extension-vs-total-conversion relationship diagram. Validates clean under `PackCompiler validate`.
- **Native-style MODS quick panel as the default click (redesigned MODS UX)** ŌĆö Clicking the injected MODS button now opens a compact, NATIVE-STYLE quick panel (`src/Runtime/UI/NativeQuickModPanel.cs`) instead of a full-screen takeover. The panel reads like a DINO sub-menu rather than a separate overlay:
  - **Native chrome by cloning.** Row/footer buttons are cloned from DINO's own menu button (the injected `DINOForge_ModsButton`, itself a clone of a native `MainMenuButton`) via `NativeUiHelper.CloneButton`, so they inherit DINO's frame, font, sprites and hover/press visuals. No synthetic full-screen canvas.
  - **Themed per active total_conversion `ui_theme`.** New `src/Runtime/UI/MenuThemeReader.cs` reads the active total_conversion pack's `ui_theme` block from disk (mirroring `MainMenuThemer`'s YAML extraction) and resolves it to Unity colors; defaults to Star Wars gold `#FFE81F`. Live-verified: panel logged `theme primary=RGBA(1.000, 0.910, 0.122, 1.000)` (SW gold) and rendered gold title/accent/ON labels.
  - **Per-pack ON/OFF toggles** wired through the injector's `OnNativePackToggled` ŌåÆ `RuntimeDriver.RequestPackToggle` ŌåÆ `ModPlatform.SetPackEnabled` (persists `disabled_packs.json`) ŌĆö the same queued path the UGUI menu uses.
  - **"Browse all" button** routes to the existing full-screen `NativeModsPage` browser for search/filter/details/deep management (live-verified: clicking it logged `NativeModsPage shown`). F10 still opens the full browser too.
  - Reuses the iter-149f per-element fixes (RectMask2D scroll viewport, live `PackDataProvider`) ŌĆö branch based off `58ef7834`.
  - Wiring in `src/Runtime/Plugin.cs`: sets `NativeMenuInjector.PacksDirectory` + `OnNativePackToggled`/`OnNativeReloadRequested`. Click path: `NativeMenuInjector.OnModsButtonClicked` ŌåÆ `TryShowQuickPanel` (default) ŌåÆ falls back to `TryShowNativeModsPage`/overlay. Verified live at MainMenu with 17 packs loaded (screenshots `docs/screenshots/mods-native-panel-20260530.png`, `mods-browse-all-20260530.png`).
- **Subpage FULL TAKEOVER ŌĆö extends the reskin beyond gold text to panels, frames and native controls.** Previously the aux/subpage path recolored only TMP text gold while panels, backgrounds, button frames and native controls (sliders, ŌŚäŌ¢║ selectors, tab rails) stayed vanilla ŌĆö so Options and the GAME/VIDEO/SOUND/CONTROLS/TWITCH tabs looked ~native. `MainMenuThemer.ApplyToAuxiliaryMenus` now applies the SAME full takeover the main menu got, generalized per-surface and driven each pump frame (self-guarded on the live canvas count so it is free until a subpage opens):
  - **Panel/background** ŌĆö injects a DINOForge-owned `DINOForge_AuxBackground` full-rect `Image` behind each subpage panel (anchored to the panel's largest container, `SetAsFirstSibling`, `raycastTarget = false` per Pattern #235) using the pack's `background_image`; falls back to a solid dark SW `background_tint` when no art ships.
  - **9-slice frames** ŌĆö applies the pack's `button_frame`/`button_frame_hover` art to every subpage button via Unity `SpriteSwap`; color-transition gold-on-dark fallback when art is absent.
  - **Native controls** ŌĆö restyles sliders (fill + handle ŌåÆ gold, track ŌåÆ dim), ŌŚäŌ¢║ selector arrow buttons and tab-rail buttons (themed frame + gold text, active/inactive via SpriteSwap), and toggles (gold checkmark) ŌĆö discovered by component type + GameObject-name hints, no hardcoded IDs.
  - **Font** ŌĆö applies the themed runtime TMP font to every subpage label and recolors remaining labels to the themed text color.
  - Surface discovery is ID-free (`IsAuxSurface`: any active non-main-menu canvas carrying a `Selectable` or a sizable panel image), respecting agent governance. All steps degrade gracefully and never throw. netstandard2.0 build exit 0.
- **EPIC-027 ŌĆö Main-menu visual takeover for total-conversion mods.** `MainMenuThemer` previously only did a cosmetic tint + label rewrite ("DINO with a color filter"). It now performs a real reskin for `total_conversion` packs that ship menu art, while keeping the tint/label path as a graceful fallback:
  - **Logo swap** ŌĆö injects a DINOForge-owned `DINOForge_ModLogo` `Image` at upper-center of the menu canvas (the pack's `logo` PNG), `raycastTarget = false` so buttons stay clickable (Pattern #235), and hides DINO's native "Diplomacy is Not an Option" title scene-wide (alphaŌåÆclear + `SetActive(false)`, matching by content across all canvases).
  - **Background swap** ŌĆö injects a DINOForge-owned full-canvas `DINOForge_ModBackground` `Image` (anchored to fill, `SetAsFirstSibling`, `raycastTarget = false`) using the pack's `background_image` PNG. DINO renders its menu backdrop as a 3D camera scene (not a UGUI Image), so the overlay approach (spec ┬¦2.4) deterministically covers the vanilla backdrop where a plain sprite-swap would not. Also swaps any existing large background Image as a belt-and-braces measure. Falls back to the prior `background_tint` when no art is supplied.
  - **Pack selection** ŌĆö only **enabled** `total_conversion` packs are eligible to theme the menu (respects the F10 mod-menu enable/disable choice; no hardcoded pack id), so when multiple total conversions are installed the user's selection decides which one takes over.
  - **Button frames** ŌĆö swaps each native `MainMenuButton : Selectable` frame `Image` to the pack's 9-slice `button_frame` / `button_frame_hover` PNGs via Unity `SpriteSwap` transition (18px insets for 256├Ś96 art, scaled proportionally).
  - Art is loaded at runtime from raw PNGs (`Texture2D.LoadImage` ŌåÆ `Sprite.Create`) shipped inside the pack at `assets/ui/` ŌĆö no Unity AssetBundle / Addressables build required for 2D menu art. New `MainMenuThemer.LoadSpriteFromPack` resolves pack-relative paths against the deployed `dinoforge_packs/<id>/` directory and returns `null` (never throws) on any failure.
  - **Schema**: `ui_theme` in `schemas/pack-manifest.schema.json` gains `logo`, `background_image`, `button_frame`, `button_frame_hover` (pack-relative PNG path strings).
  - **Packs**: `warfare-starwars` and `warfare-modern` `pack.yaml` `ui_theme` blocks now reference the new art (Modern also gains a full `ui_theme` block).
  - **Art pipeline**: `scripts/art/rasterize-menu-takeover.ps1` rasterizes each pack's source `assets/svg/` menu art (logo / full-bleed background / button frames) into the `assets/ui/` PNGs the pack ships (auto-detects inkscape/resvg/rsvg-convert/magick). Star Wars ships `menu_logo.png` (gold "CLONE WARS" lockup, 1600├Ś600), `menu_bg.png` (deep-space hyperspace starfield, 1920├Ś1080), `btn_normal.png` / `btn_hover.png` (holo-durasteel 9-slice frames).
  - **Menu font swap** ŌĆö `ui_theme.font` (pack-relative TTF path, optional `font_family`) is loaded at runtime: the shipped TTF is registered process-privately via Win32 `AddFontResourceEx (FR_PRIVATE)`, rasterized through `Font.CreateDynamicFontFromOSFont`, and wrapped into a TMP `TMP_FontAsset` via reflection (Runtime has no compile-time TMPro ref) ŌĆö picking the richest `CreateFontAsset(Font, ŌĆ”)` overload with real atlas params (samplingPointSize 90, padding 9, 1024┬▓ atlas, SDFAA render mode, Dynamic population) ŌĆö then assigned to every `TMP_Text` on the menu canvas. `warfare-starwars` ships `menu_font.ttf` (Kenney Future Narrow, CC0). NOTE: in-game the art reskin (logo + background + 14 gold button frames) applies fully and is verified by screenshot, but `TMP_FontAsset.CreateFontAsset` returns null for an OS-dynamic source font in DINO's TMP runtime (both 1-arg and 8-arg overloads), so the custom font does not yet render (`font=False`); the art takeover is unaffected.
  - **Sprite/font path diagnostic** ŌĆö `LoadSpriteFromPack` now logs the **absolute path** it tried on both hit (`takeover art LOADED: '<abs>'`) and miss (`takeover art MISSING ŌĆö tried abs path: '<abs>' (packsDir=ŌĆ”, packId=ŌĆ”, rel=ŌĆ”)`); the takeover summary line reports `font=<bool>` and per-overload `CreateFontAsset` results. This diagnostic confirmed the art paths resolve correctly to `dinoforge_packs/warfare-starwars/assets/ui/*.png` ŌĆö i.e. takeover sprites were NOT returning null due to a path bug; the earlier tint-only fallbacks were a pack-selection issue (a competing enabled `total_conversion` winning) rather than a path-resolution one.
- **EPIC-027 ŌĆö Themed loading-screen takeover for total_conversion packs** ŌĆö DINO previously had no DINOForge-branded loading screen; the only overlay was a plain dark `ModLoadingOverlay`. New `src/Runtime/UI/LoadingScreenController.cs` renders a full-screen themed loading screen on a DontDestroyOnLoad ScreenSpaceOverlay canvas (`sortingOrder 9998`, below DFCanvas/32767, above DINO's loader): pack background sprite + logo + rotating tip/lore text + animated progress bar + spinner + version label.
  - **Declarative, no C# per pack** ŌĆö driven entirely from `pack.yaml` `ui_theme.loading_screen` (`background`, `logo`, `tips`, `tip_rotation_seconds`, `accent_color`, `overlay_opacity`) with a `ui_theme.loading_background` shorthand. The controller does a lightweight pre-scan of the deployed `dinoforge_packs/` directory (respecting `disabled_packs.json`) for the first active `type: total_conversion` pack that declares a loading background; falls back to the built-in DINOForge dark theme if none is found or the image is missing (graceful degradation, never throws).
  - **Lifecycle hooks** ŌĆö created in `RuntimeDriver.Initialize` (replacing `ModLoadingOverlay`); shown during the game's own asset-load window via `Plugin.OnActiveSceneChanged` (`InitialGameLoader` / first scene) and faded out (0.5s `CanvasGroup` fade, then destroy) when packs finish loading, the ECS world is ready, or the `MainMenu` scene activates. Because DINO loads MainMenu **additively** (no `activeSceneChanged`), the MainMenu fade-out also fires from `OnSceneLoaded` ŌĆö the missing main-thread hook.
  - **Mono/netstandard2.0 safe** ŌĆö no TMPro, no `Update()` (DINO replaces the PlayerLoop): tip rotation, spinner spin, and smooth progress all run from a `WaitForEndOfFrame` coroutine using `Time.unscaledDeltaTime`; background sprites loaded via `File.ReadAllBytes` + `Texture2D.LoadImage` (no Addressables at load time).
  - **SDK / schema** ŌĆö new `PackLoadingScreen` model + `LoadingScreen` / `LoadingBackground` on `PackUiTheme` (`src/SDK/PackManifest.cs`); `schemas/pack-manifest.schema.json` `ui_theme` extended with `loading_screen` (typed, `additionalProperties:false`) and `loading_background`.
  - **Star Wars theme** ŌĆö `packs/warfare-starwars/pack.yaml` declares a Clone Wars loading screen; background + logo rasterized (rsvg-convert) from `assets/svg/ui/loading-republic.svg` (1920├Ś1080) and `assets/svg/logo-title.svg` into `assets/loading/`, auto-deployed by the existing `DeployPacks` target.
  - Spec: `docs/design/loading-screen-system.md`.

### Fixed
- **Per-element engine-UI bugs after steam_appid fix (iter-149f)** ŌĆö With the UI now loading, each element had an individual rendering bug. All verified fixed live at the MainMenu (before/after screenshots in `docs/screenshots/`):
  - **MODS page listed zero packs.** The native MODS button routes through `ContextualModMenuHost ŌåÆ NativeMainMenuModMenu`, whose pack cache is only filled by `SetPacks`. `ModPlatform.UpdateUI` pushes packs to the overlay host it owns, never to this contextual host, so the INSTALLED PACKS list stayed empty despite 11 loaded packs. Added a `PackDataProvider` to `NativeMainMenuModMenu` (wired to `ModPlatform.GetLoadedPackDisplayInfos` in `TryWireNativeMenuInjectorHost`) that pulls fresh packs in `Show()`; also wired the injector-level `PackDataProvider` for the secondary `TryShowNativeModsPage` path. The MODS page now lists all packs with name/version/type/ON-OFF status and a fully populated detail pane on selection.
  - **F9 debug panel body was blank.** The viewport used a stencil `Mask` backed by a fully-transparent `Image`; on DINO's Mono/Unity build that stencil was never written, masking out **all** scroll content (header rendered, body empty). Switched `UiBuilder.MakeScrollView` to `RectMask2D` (rect-based clip, no graphic-alpha dependency). F9 now shows Platform Status (Version/FPS/GC Heap/Bridge/packs), ECS Worlds (entity & system counts), and the collapsible Systems/Archetypes sections.
  - **F10 mod-menu pack list was empty + a stretched green bar overlapped FILTERS.** Two bugs: (1) the FILTERS `AccentBar` was a flex child of a `HorizontalLayoutGroup` and got stretched into a large green bar ŌĆö fixed with `LayoutElement.ignoreLayout`; (2) the pack-list scroll got zero height because the ListPane `VerticalLayoutGroup` had `childControlHeight=false`, ignoring the scroll's `flexibleHeight=1` ŌĆö enabled `childControlHeight` and pinned the scroll to top after rebuild. Combined with the `RectMask2D` viewport fix, the F10 list now renders its rows, and the Tier/State/Sort dropdowns display correctly.
- **In-game theme showed MODERN instead of STAR WARS (active-conversion selection was order-dependent)** ŌĆö `MainMenuThemer.TryApplyTheme` picked the *first* `total_conversion` pack (with a `ui_theme:` block) in `Directory.GetDirectories` order, which is alphabetical; with both `warfare-modern` and `warfare-starwars` active, `warfare-modern` sorted first and won the main-menu theme even when Star Wars was intended. Two-part fix: (1) cut the roster so `warfare-starwars` is the sole active `total_conversion`; (2) hardened selection in `src/Runtime/UI/MainMenuThemer.cs` to be order-independent and disabled-aware ŌĆö it now restricts candidates to **enabled** packs (`IsEnabled == true`, so a `*.disabled` total_conversion can never be themed), then deterministically picks the lexicographically-smallest enabled `total_conversion` that declares a `ui_theme:` block (falling back to the smallest enabled `total_conversion` otherwise). Live-verified: `dinoforge_debug.log` shows `Theme applied: 'STAR WARS'` and only the `republic`/`cis` factions registered (no Modern `western_alliance`/`classic_enemy` content); main-menu screenshot at `docs/screenshots/pack-cut-sw-active-20260530.png` shows the CLONE WARS / GALACTIC CONFLICT title.
- **Dangling `tools/phenotype-journeys` submodule gitlink** ŌĆö The repo carried a registered submodule gitlink (mode 160000 ŌåÆ commit `dd1ff8a3`) with a `.gitmodules` entry pointing at a repo that was not initialized/cloneable, leaving an empty placeholder directory and tripping submodule-aware git operations. Removed the dangling pointer cleanly (`git submodule deinit -f` + `git rm` of the gitlink and the now-empty `.gitmodules`); no hook bypass.

### Changed
- **Pack roster cut to the focus set** ŌĆö Disabled all non-focus packs by renaming their directories to `*.disabled` (the `FileDiscoveryService` loader skips any dir ending in `.disabled`), in both the repo `packs/` tree and the deployed `BepInEx/dinoforge_packs/`. Disabled: `economy-balanced`, `example-hello-world`, `example-total-conversion`, `example-ui-counter`, `ui-hud-minimal`, `vanilla-dino`, `warfare-modern` (`scenario-tutorial` was already disabled). **Active set is now exactly `warfare-aerial`, `warfare-naval`, `warfare-starwars` (+ framework).** Resolved a stale deployed `warfare-modern` / `warfare-modern.disabled` duplicate by keeping the newer copy (the one carrying the menu-takeover `ui_theme:` block) as the single `warfare-modern.disabled` and sending the older stale duplicate to the Recycle Bin. Nothing was permanently deleted.

### Fixed (assets)
- **Star Wars bundles shipped primitive-placeholder prefabs instead of real meshes (#101/#947)** ŌĆö The shipped `warfare-starwars` AssetBundles wired 64/75 bundle prefabs to Unity built-in primitive meshes (Cube/Capsule/Sphere, `fileID:10202`), so even a perfect in-game Harmony swap rendered cubes. Root cause: `*.fbx`/`*.glb`/`*.obj` are gitignored, so in a fresh worktree the only committed mesh source is `packs/warfare-starwars/assets/raw/<asset_id>/model.glb` (the `!packs/*/assets/raw/*/model.glb` allowlist); the intended pipeline (`convert_models.py` Blender GLBŌåÆFBX ŌåÆ `GenerateStarWarsPrefabsFromModels` ŌåÆ `BuildAssetBundles`) was never reproduced end-to-end in the worktree, and the primitive-only generators (`GenerateStarWarsPrefabs.cs`/`BuildAll.cs`, which *skip existing* prefabs) had poisoned the prefab dir. Fixes:
  - Added `unity-assetbundle-builder/convert_real_models.py` ŌĆö worktree-relative Blender converter that imports only the **real** committed GLBs (vertex-count gate skips the 21 stub `model.glb` files that are 896/1092-byte, 8ŌĆō24-vertex placeholders) into `Assets/Models/*.fbx`. Result: 15 real FBX (855ŌĆō104,389 verts) converted, 21 stubs correctly skipped.
  - Remapped three `GenerateStarWarsPrefabsFromModels.cs` `ModelName` entries to real meshes that were previously unmapped: `sw-rep-at-te-walker`ŌåÆ`sw_aat_walker`, `sw-cis-spider-droid`ŌåÆ`cis_probe_droid`, `sw-rep-clone-commander`ŌåÆ`rep_clone_militia`.
  - Regenerated all prefabs from the real FBX (Unity 2021.3.45f1 batchmode, `-noUpm`): **14 of 36 SW unit/building bundle keys now reference real MeshFilter/MeshRenderer + materials** (the rest fall back to primitives only where no real source GLB exists in the repo).
  - Rebuilt the AssetBundles and updated the 3 newly-real bundles in `packs/warfare-starwars/assets/bundles/`: `sw-cis-spider-droid` 43,768BŌåÆ1,467,170B, `sw-rep-clone-commander` 44,382BŌåÆ207,814B, `sw-rep-at-te-walker` 44,197BŌåÆ96,885B (the other 11 real-mesh bundles were already real). Bundle-mesh content externally verified by loading the rebuilt bundles back in Unity (`VerifyBundleMesh`): spider-droid maxVerts=48,515, clone-commander 8 meshes maxVerts=1,751, at-te-walker 36 meshes, droideka maxVerts=65,541 ŌĆö vs the primitive control `sw-rep-clone-pilot` at a single 550-vert capsule. Deployed to the live game pack and verified by SHA-256 match.
  - **Ceiling note**: only 15 of the 36 SW source `model.glb` files contain real geometry in the repo; the remaining 21 are stub placeholders and cannot be wired to real meshes without re-sourcing the upstream assets (the deeper asset-sourcing half of #101, out of scope here).

### Fixed (runtime)
- **Update-check threw `MethodNotFound: JToken.ToString(Newtonsoft.Json.Formatting)` at runtime** ŌĆö `RuntimeDriver` logged `[RuntimeDriver] Update check result delivery failed: ... Method not found: string Newtonsoft.Json.Linq.JToken.ToString(Newtonsoft.Json.Formatting)` whenever the update check tried to persist its 24-hour throttle timestamp. Root cause: `UpdateChecker.PersistLastCheck()` called the `JToken.ToString(Formatting)` **instance** overload, which is absent from the Unity-bundled, stripped `Newtonsoft.Json` 13.0.2 (`<game>_Data/Managed/Newtonsoft.Json.dll`) that the Runtime both compiles and runs against in the BepInEx/Mono context (a second, full 13.0.4 copy lives in `BepInEx/plugins/`). Fix (`src/Runtime/Updates/UpdateChecker.cs:294`): use the version-stable static `JsonConvert.SerializeObject(state, Formatting.None)` instead ŌĆö the same static API the JSON-RPC bridge already uses successfully. Audited all of `src/Runtime` for sibling version-fragile Newtonsoft instance overloads; this was the only `.ToString(Formatting)` call (all other serialization already uses static `JsonConvert.SerializeObject`).
- **Aviation ECS systems crashed every frame: "This method should have been replaced by codegen"** ŌĆö `AerialMovementSystem`, `AerialTargetingSystem`, and `AerialSpawnSystem` each used `Entities.ForEach(...).WithoutBurst().Run()` in their `OnUpdate`. `Entities.ForEach`/`Job.WithCode` REQUIRE the Unity.Entities DOTS source generator, which only runs inside the Unity Editor's compilation pipeline. `DINOForge.Runtime` is built `netstandard2.0` outside the editor (`dotnet build`), so codegen never replaces the lambda placeholder and it throws at runtime ŌĆö flooding the log every simulation frame once `SimulationSystemGroup` ticks. Fixed by rewriting all three `OnUpdate` methods to the established manual `EntityQuery` pattern (cache the query in `OnCreate` with `EntityQueryOptions.IncludePrefab`, iterate `ToEntityArray(Allocator.Temp)`, `EntityManager.Get/SetComponentData`) ŌĆö the same codegen-free approach used by `EntityQueries.cs` / `AssetSwapSystem.cs`. No `Entities.ForEach`/`Job.WithCode` remains anywhere in `src/Runtime/Aviation/`. Behavior (altitude lerp, nearest-enemy targeting, spawn-at-altitude, anti-air building sweep) is preserved exactly.
- **DINO self-relaunch via Steam killed the BepInEx-injected process (no MODS button/F9/F10)** ŌĆö On startup DINO re-launches itself through Steam unless a `steam_appid.txt` (AppID `1272320`) sits beside the exe; that Steam relaunch terminates the BepInEx-injected process, so the MODS button and F9/F10 panels never appear. Fixed by auto-provisioning `steam_appid.txt` (UTF-8, no BOM, no trailing newline ŌĆö 7 bytes) on **deploy** (new `DeploySteamAppId` MSBuild target in `src/Runtime/DINOForge.Runtime.csproj`, runs on every `DeployToGame=true` build) and on **launch** (`_ensure_steam_appid` guard in the MCP `game_launch`/`game_launch_test` tools, plus `/launch-game` step 2b). Steam "Verify Integrity" can delete the file; deploy + launch both re-create it idempotently.
- **Engine-UI revive: two remaining upstream blockers (iter-149b)** ŌĆö Prior fixes moved resurrection to main-thread consumers, but the engine UI (MODS/F9/F10) still never loaded entering MainMenu. Live `dinoforge_debug.log` showed the resurrection heartbeat stopping (no #24) right after `OnDestroy`, and `activeSceneChanged` firing only for `''` and `InitialGameLoader` ŌĆö **never** for MainMenu. Two precisely-localized blockers, both fixed in `src/Runtime/Plugin.cs`:
  - **Blocker 1 ŌĆö bg fallback wedges on pipe restart.** `ResurrectionFallbackLoop` called `SharedBridgeServer.EnsureServerAlive()` at the top of every iteration, which does a pipe `Stop()`ŌåÆ`Start()` (NamedPipeServerStream dispose + fresh thread) whenever the bridge thread is dead ŌĆö always true right after `RequestShutdown()`. That pipe teardown/recreate blocked the background thread during the `InitialGameLoaderŌåÆMainMenu` asset load, starving the resurrection heartbeat (the deadlock did not disappear in 6be0f5e3 ŌĆö it *moved* from `TryResurrect` to the pipe restart). Fix: removed the pipe call from the fallback loop; pipe keepalive is now owned by (a) the main-thread PlayerLoop `%60` gate and (b) a new dedicated `PipeKeepAliveLoop` background thread that may block on pipe I/O without affecting resurrection heartbeats. The fallback loop now does pure managed work only and, on grace-window elapse, **only MARKs** `NeedsDeferredResurrection` (no bg-thread Unity ECalls) for a main-thread consumer to execute.
  - **Blocker 2 (keystone) ŌĆö MainMenu emits no `activeSceneChanged`.** DINO loads MainMenu additively / without changing the active scene, so `activeSceneChanged` stayed silent for it while both main-thread revive hooks (PlayerLoop marker + `activeSceneChanged`) were dead. Fix: added a `SceneManager.sceneLoaded` subscription (fires for additive loads), logging scene name + buildIndex + load mode on every scene event, and routed both scene events through a shared main-thread `MainThreadReviveIfNeeded()` that performs the actual `TryResurrect` on the Unity main thread (where `Camera.main`/`AddComponent`/`Initialize` ECalls are safe) ŌåÆ `RuntimeDriver.Initialize` ŌåÆ `RunMainMenuInit` ŌåÆ MODS/F9/F10. Engine UI no longer depends solely on the PlayerLoop marker surviving DINO's MainMenu PlayerLoop rebuild; `OnPlayerLoopSet` now logs whether re-injection re-added the marker. `ENGINE-UI READY` is mirrored to `dinoforge_debug.log` for live verification. Event handlers are static (survive BepInEx object teardown by design ŌĆö Pattern #105 paired-by-design); all paths log + never throw (Pattern #104/#111).
- **Engine-UI injection race ("no Mods button / F9-F10 panels don't work")** ŌĆö The MODS button and F9/F10 panels intermittently failed to load. Root cause: the only path that loaded packs and wired the mod menu was gated on an ECS World, but DINO has **no ECS World at the main menu** (worlds are created only when entering gameplay), so engine-UI setup was timing-dependent and often never ran. Additionally, native button injection required a `UnityEngine.UI.Button` while DINO's menu uses a custom `MainMenuButton : Selectable`. Fixes:
  - `RuntimeDriver.RunMainMenuInit(reason)` ŌĆö deterministic, idempotent main-menu init that loads packs (pure YAML, no ECS world), wires UGUI, pushes packs to the F10 panel, and attempts native injection. All failures are logged (no silent swallow ŌĆö Pattern #104/#111).
  - **Self-healing**: re-runs the menu-mode init on `SceneManager.activeSceneChanged`, plus a bounded per-frame retry (`MenuInitMaxRetryFrames`) that re-attempts MODS-button injection until it succeeds ŌĆö closing the intermittent timing window.
  - `NativeMenuInjector.IsModsButtonInjected` accessor drives the retry loop; the existing `Selectable`-donor injection path (custom `MainMenuButton`) is preserved.
  - **Launch heartbeat**: a single `[DINOForge] ENGINE-UI READY: packs=<n> modsButton=<bool> f9=<bool> f10=<bool>` line is emitted in the BepInEx console so engine-UI state is confirmable at a glance.
  - Fixed a pre-existing build break: two call sites referenced the renamed `NativeModsPage.OnBackPressed` (now `OnBackClicked`).
  - Added `EngineUiSelfHealCharacterizationTests` (6 source-text invariant fixtures) pinning the anti-race guarantees.
- **Resurrection-fallback grace window never completing (FailureMode B)** ŌĆö On the `InitialGameLoader` scene the `RuntimeDriver` tears down and sets `NeedsResurrection`. The background `ResurrectionFallbackLoop` correctly *detected* the need every cycle ("starting grace timer") but the 4000ms grace window **never elapsed**, so `TryResurrect` was detected-but-never-executed and the driver stayed dormant (no MODS button / dead F9/F10). Root cause: the grace timer (`lastNeedsObservedUtc`) was a **local variable**; any loop re-entry reset it to `MinValue`, restarting the window before it could fire. Fixes (`src/Runtime/Plugin.cs`):
  - Latched the grace **deadline** in a static field (`_graceDeadlineUtc`, lock-guarded) so a loop restart **resumes** the in-progress window instead of resetting it (`IsGraceWindowElapsed` / `RearmGraceDeadline` / `ResetGraceDeadline`).
  - `NeedsResurrection` is now cleared **only when the revive actually brings a live, initialized `RuntimeDriver` online** (`ResurrectionSucceeded`); a partial/failed revive retains the need and re-arms the window for another attempt (no silent drop).
  - The revive path lands on the active (menu) scene and `RuntimeDriver.Initialize` ŌåÆ `RunMainMenuInit` so MODS/F9/F10 come up post-resurrection.
  - Added `ResurrectionGraceWindowTests` (4 characterization tests) pinning the deadline-persists-across-restart invariant.
- **Resurrection wedged on the background thread (FailureMode B deadlock)** ŌĆö Even with the grace window fixed, the engine UI (MODS/F9/F10) still failed to appear because resurrection was being *executed* on the `ResurrectionFallback` **background thread** (via `GameBridgeServer.EnsureServerAlive` ŌåÆ `TryResurrect`). `TryResurrect` touches Unity ECalls (`Camera.main` / `AddComponent` / `RuntimeDriver.Initialize`, which reach Resources/asset APIs); per the documented rule "Resources.* from a bg thread DEADLOCKS during asset loading", the fallback thread **wedged silently** during the `InitialGameLoaderŌåÆMainMenu` asset load ŌĆö heartbeats stopped, the revive never fired, and the driver stayed dormant. Fixes (`src/Runtime/Plugin.cs`, `src/Runtime/Bridge/GameBridgeServer.cs`):
  - Resurrection is now executed on **main-thread consumers**: (1) `OnActiveSceneChanged` calls `TryResurrect` directly after the new scene is active (main thread); (2) a new static `ConsumeResurrectionOnMainThread()` is driven from the Harmony-injected PlayerLoop `Update` (main thread, survives RuntimeDriver teardown, throttled to once/sec via the existing `%60` gate, idempotent + cap-guarded, never throws into the PlayerLoop ŌĆö Pattern #104/#111).
  - `GameBridgeServer.EnsureServerAlive` (background thread) **no longer calls `TryResurrect`** ŌĆö it only restarts the dead pipe **server thread** (pipe-only work, no Unity ECalls) and calls `Plugin.MarkNeedsDeferredResurrection`, leaving the actual revive to the main-thread consumers.
  - The background `ResurrectionFallbackLoop` remains as a last-resort grace-windowed safety net (and still must not make Unity ECalls).
  - Need flags (`NeedsResurrection` / `NeedsDeferredResurrection` / `s_rootJustDestroyed`) are cleared only on confirmed success (`ResurrectionSucceeded`), and a revive landing on a menu scene runs `RunMainMenuInit` so MODS/F9/F10 come up post-resurrection.
- **Prebuilt TMP SDF font for Star Wars main menu** ŌĆö `TMP_FontAsset.CreateFontAsset()`
  returns `null` at runtime inside DINO for OS-dynamic fonts (the Mono atlas-generator
  path is unavailable in the shipped player). The SW menu font is now baked offline in
  Unity 2021.3.45f1 (Option A): `unity-assetbundle-builder/Assets/Editor/BakeTmpFontAsset.cs`
  generates a static SDF atlas + glyph table and tags it for the version-locked
  `sw_menu_font` AssetBundle. `scripts/game/bake-sw-menu-font.ps1` drives the bake +
  bundle build + copy into the pack. `warfare-starwars/pack.yaml` `ui_theme.font` /
  `font_asset_name` point at the prebuilt asset, and `MainMenuThemer` now LOADS the
  prebuilt `TMP_FontAsset` from the bundle (reflection, no compile-time TMPro ref) and
  applies `font` + `fontSharedMaterial` to every menu `TMP_Text` instead of calling
  `CreateFontAsset` at runtime.

- Stale `NativeModsPage.OnBackPressed` references (renamed field is `OnBackClicked`) in
  `NativeMainMenuModMenu.cs` and `NativeMenuInjector.cs` that broke the netstandard2.0 build (#965).

